{
  "text": "2.6. Cytotoxic Activity 2.6.1. Cell Culture. We purchased mouse fibroblasts NIH/3T3 (ATCC5 CRL-16586) cell lines from American Type Culture Collection (ATCC) CCL-1658. We chose the NIH/3T3 cells because they are widely used as an in vitro model for a tissue model. Therefore, if the material tested is cytotoxic on this cell, its use in therapy is discouraged [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . This cellular lineage was grown in plastic flasks (25 cm 2 ) with RPMI 1640 medium, supplemented with 10% inactivated fetal bovine serum and 1% antibiotic/antimycotic solution [CITATION_4] . The cultures were incubated at 37 \u2218 C in an atmosphere containing 5% CO 2 [CITATION_5] . Medium was changed every 48 h, and when the culture reached confluence, the subculture was treated with Trypsin-EDTA, until complete release of the cells. The released cells were transferred to a new plastic flask or 96-well plates [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] . [CITATION_9] . Before testing, we dispersed different concentrations of all formulations in culture medium without fetal bovine serum and antibiotic/antimycotic solution. We plated NIH/3T3 cells on 96-well plates [CITATION_10] [CITATION_11] [CITATION_12] . We used 1 \u00d7 10 5 cells\u22c5mL \u22121 to 1 \u00d7 10 7 cells\u22c5mL \u22121 per well [CITATION_13] . After this, we incubated the plate at 37 \u2218 C, in a humidified incubator with 5% CO 2 , for 24 h [CITATION_14] . Then, the medium was replaced and the test repeated with different formulations concentrations in the range between 5 and 200 g\u22c5mL \u22121 , which was added to the wells in triplicate for each concentration. We used DL50 to define the CCN cytotoxicity (50% of the cells died) [CITATION_15] [CITATION_16] [CITATION_17] .",
